{"abstract": "Suppose it is 2011 and the so-called Volcker Act has become law, curtailing banks\u2019 riskier activities, like hedge funds and proprietary trading.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/25/business/25views.html", "snippet": "Suppose it is 2011 and the so-called Volcker Act has become law, curtailing banks\u2019 riskier activities, like hedge funds and proprietary trading.", "lead_paragraph": "Suppose it is 2011 and the so-called Volcker Act has recently become law, sharply curtailing banks\u2019 riskier activities, like hedge funds and proprietary trading, and separating those activities from consumer businesses and retail deposits. Citigroup\u2019s recently arrived chief executive, Bob Steel, formerly of Wachovia, is dismantling the group to comply with the law. A memo to the bank\u2019s staff announces that Tim Geithner has been hired as head of the bank\u2019s strategy and investor relations. Oddly, this imaginary situation is not such a stretch. ", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "2", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2010/01/25/business/25views_CA0/thumbStandard.jpg", "height": 75, "width": 75, "subType": "thumbnail", "crop_name": "thumbStandard", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2010/01/25/business/25views_CA0/thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": 75, "thumbnailheight": 75}}], "headline": {"main": "Citibank in 2011, Hypothetically", "kicker": "Reuters BreakingViews", "content_kicker": null, "print_headline": "Citibank in 2011, Hypothetically", "name": null, "seo": null, "sub": null}, "keywords": [{"name": "organizations", "value": "CITIBANK", "rank": 1, "major": "N"}, {"name": "organizations", "value": "Citigroup Inc", "rank": 2, "major": "N"}, {"name": "subject", "value": "Regulation and Deregulation of Industry", "rank": 3, "major": "N"}, {"name": "persons", "value": "Bernanke, Ben S", "rank": 4, "major": "N"}, {"name":